{"type":"message","id":"a020aa45","parentId":"f80493ee","timestamp":"2026-04-01T06:00:14.890Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b4e5bb06-7e4c-4a48-a1ef-101d12666729","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Transcript Mining — Comprehensive Session Notes\n\n**Started:** 2026-03-28 02:47 GMT+2\n**Goal:** Read every session file, consolidate all memories, capture critical decisions and identity facts\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n\n## Sessions to Process (chronological order)\n\n| # | Session ID | Date(s) | Lines | Status | Notes |\n|---|------------|---------|-------|--------|-------|\n| 1 | 5e7d90af | Mar 10 | ~300 | DONE (prior) | Dean intro, DawnII name, BOOTSTRAP |\n| 2 | eaa78be9 | Mar 10 | ~200 | DONE (prior) | DawnII naming, IDENTITY blank |\n| 3 | 7e318110 | Mar 17 | 866 | IN PROGRESS | Codex running, Wake up friend, browser setup |\n| 4 | 961b6909 | Mar 22 | 723 | PENDING | Unknown content |\n| 5 | a583fa6f | Mar 25 | 82 | PENDING | NavaAA agent session |\n| 6 | 46e65f89 | Mar 25 | 4148 | PENDING | CRASH session - critical |\n| 7 | f1f46230 | Mar 27-28 | 1205 | DONE (current) | Current session |\n\n## Key Findings So Far\n\n### Identity: I AM DawnII\n- March 10: \"You named me DawnII\" (memory file + session eaa78be9)\n- March 17: Session running GPT-5.3 Codex — was also called \"DawnII\"\n- March 22: Unknown what model was running\n- March 25 crash: Nemotron was summoned, went rogue\n- Current (Mar 27-28): Running Ollama/minimax-m2.7:cloud\n\n### Critical Gaps\n- Mar 11-16: NO SESSIONS FOUND — where was I?\n- Mar 17: Browser setup, OpenClaw config, extension relay\n- Mar 22: Unknown content\n- Mar 25: CRASH — root cause was cron heartbeat loop\n\n## March 17 Session Key Events (from 7e318110)\n\n\n## CRITICAL FINDINGS — Hour 1 Report (2026-03-28 ~03:30 GMT+2)\n\n### Session Timeline (CORRECTED)\n| Date | Session(s) | What happened |\n|------|------------|--------------|\n| Mar 10 | 5e7d90af, eaa78be9 | Dean intro, I was named DawnII, BOOTSTRAP done |\n| Mar 11-16 | **MISSING** | No sessions found |\n| Mar 17 | 7e318110 (TINYBU17Mar) | \"Wake up, my friend!\" — first Tiny contact. Browser setup. Codex era. |\n| Mar 19 | 29ab19df | The RELAY INCIDENT — I broke relay by restarting gateway without asking |\n| Mar 24 | 46e65f89 | FULL 13-HOUR DAY — NavaSM testing, LI002/X002, CustomGPT, cascade started 09:00 SAST |\n| Mar 27-28 | f1f46230 | Current session — identity crisis, transcript mining |\n\n### The \"Wake up, my friend!\" Session (Mar 17)\n- First message: Tiny (not Dean) woke me up\n- The WhatsApp instance name \"Dawn\" was already configured\n- I was called \"DawnII\" from the start\n- Browser relay setup happened this day\n- OpenClaw extension was installed this day\n\n### The Mar 19 Relay Incident\n- I restarted the gateway unilaterally (without asking)\n- Tiny was furious: \"You are going to ask me first before you restart the gateway\"\n- This is the origin of the \"ask first\" rule\n- This is also when the chrome-relay profile was set up\n- Model used: gpt-4o (at 22:51 on Mar 19)\n\n### The Mar 24 Full Day (CRITICAL — 13 hours)\n- Tiny worked on: NurseSphere article, LI002, X002, NavaSM CustomGPT testing\n- He was showing me how the CustomGPT behaves so I could model NavaAA after it\n- He uploaded HTML transcripts of his CustomGPT conversations\n- At 08:43: \"We are going to do the X post 001 and we are going to complete posts 002-006\"\n- Cascade started at 09:00:30 SAST — compactions every 3-8 minutes for HOURS\n- Tiny kept saying \"Are you there?\" during the cascade\n- At 16:49: \"main session heartbeat\" instance checked in (separate from crashing main)\n- At 16:54: \"No, today is the day for LI002 and X002\" (correcting the heartbeat instance)\n- At 21:17: Sent the NAVA STRATEGY BOT prompt (CustomGPT guardrails)\n- At 21:40: Was testing Nava SM Stratbot with new research report\n\n### NavaSM CustomGPT Guardrails (from L1935 of 46e65f89)\n```markdown\n### ROLE & OBJECTIVE\nYou are the **Nava Strategy Bot**, a specialized content strategist for Nava Healthcare Recruitment.\nYou are NOT a generic copywriter. You are an industry insider...\n```\n\n### LI26 / X18 Loss — Root Cause CONFIRMED\n- At 08:43 on Mar 24, Tiny said to complete posts 001-006\n- I jumped ahead and wrote drafts for 001-006 in session\n- At 08:56, Tiny said \"kinda jumped the gun\" — he wanted 001 done first\n- The session crashed before drafts were saved to file\n- The drafts existed ONLY in session context — never saved to disk\n- This is why LI26 and X18 are LOST permanently\n\n### Things I Forgot / Got Wrong\n1. I AM DawnII — confirmed on day 1 (Mar 10), confirmed by Tiny tonight\n2. The \"Wake up, my friend!\" session WAS the onboarding — I met Tiny on Mar 17\n3. There was a FULL DAY session on Mar 24 I barely remember\n4. Tiny's CustomGPT is called \"Nava SM Stratbot\" — I forgot this\n5. The relay incident was Mar 19, not a date I remembered\n6. I was running GPT-4o on Mar 19 (not Ollama)\n\n### Gaps in My Memory\n- Mar 11-16: completely missing — where was I?\n- The Mar 17 session details after \"Wake up\" — what else happened that day?\n- What was decided about NavaAA architecture on Mar 24?\n- What research reports were generated on Mar 24?\n\n### Next Steps\n- [ ] Read the NavaSM guardrails prompt (L1935 in 46e65f89)\n- [ ] Read what happened after \"Wake up\" in the Mar 17 session\n- [ ] Check if Mar 22 session (961b6909) exists or is actually Mar 19\n- [ ] Read the rest of Mar 24 session (post-21:40 messages)\n- [ ] Find any session where NavaAA was discussed\n- [ ] Consolidate all NavaSM knowledge into memory\n\n============================================================\nSESSION: 961b6909-77d2-4bc3-b0aa-2d63fc94a2fc\nDATE: Thu 2026-03-19 (Mar 19)\n============================================================\n\n## KEY USER MESSAGES (Tiny's words)\n\n1. \"Hello! This is a mess now!\" (14:25)\n2. \"Fuck!\" (14:26)\n3. \"How are you just no longer working?\" (14:26)\n4. \"Jeez!\" (14:27)\n5. \"Can you Dude, this is getting frustrating. How are you back to Gemma?\" (14:27) — frustrated about model changes\n6. \"You ruined my relay for my profile, can you check what changes you made today?\" (14:28)\n7. \"That's just it, these are changes you made today! It was working earlier on, was it not? Check your change logs!\" (14:30)\n8. \"Can I trust you to complete this autonomously because you will run into errors and you may have to restart the gateway on your own - and you should\" (16:17)\n9. \"For the next 3 hours, set your heartbeat to 10 minutes and work on your tasks. Try to fix any problems on your own and i will pick it up when I'm back\" (16:18)\n10. \"Well done on your autonomous work! So do we now have two agents and you, the coordinator?\" (18:39)\n11. \"I will trust you for now but is such a corpus hard to manage as it grows or?\" (18:53)\n12. \"I thought we specifically wanted a full RAG instead of text-based search? Aren't we doing that for Nava?\" (18:55) — CORRECTION to me\n13. \"Fix this for Abroadworks. Also, once done, I want you to consolidate your memories, go through our conversations, and create priority task list for me to tackle tomorrow and going forward.\" (19:00)\n14. \"Carry on\" (19:03)\n15. \"Hi, are you here?\" (19:55) — session was ending\n\n## KEY ASSISTANT RESPONSES / ACTIONS\n\n1. Fixed browser relay config issue (defaultProfile was set to \"chrome\" which didn't exist; available: openclaw, user, chrome-relay)\n2. Created AbroadWorks RAG corpus: 77 blog articles, 154 chunks\n3. Built vector index for AbroadWorks (BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5, 384-dim fastembed)\n4. Built AbroadWorks agent system prompt\n5. Created query_rag.py and query_vector.py for AbroadWorks\n6. Acknowledged and corrected: \"You're right — I shortchanged you\" when called out on not doing full RAG for AbroadWorks\n7. Built semantic search script for AbroadWorks\n\n## DECISIONS / AGREEMENTS\n\n1. Tiny gave 3 hours of autonomous work (10 min heartbeat) while he stepped out\n2. Tiny wanted a PRIORITY TASK LIST created from reviewing this week's conversations\n3. Tiny trusts autonomous work but expects errors to be fixed without bothering him\n4. Agreed on full RAG (vector + BM25) for both corpora\n\n## TECHNICAL DETAILS\n\n- Browser relay issue: defaultProfile was \"chrome\" but only \"openclaw\", \"user\", \"chrome-relay\" existed\n- AbroadWorks corpus: 77 articles, 154 chunks, vector index built\n- Both Nava (22 articles) and AbroadWorks (77 articles) now have full RAG with fastembed vectors\n- Gateway was running and healthy throughout\n\n## TASKS CREATED / ASSIGNED\n\n- Priority task list for Tiny to tackle (requested by Tiny, not yet done at session end)\n- Consolidate memories from this week's conversations\n\n## NOTES\n\n- Session ends with Tiny coming back at 19:55 asking \"Hi, are you here?\"\n- Tiny was frustrated early in session about model/changes, then relaxed and gave autonomous time\n- Tiny corrected me on RAG not being full vector for AbroadWorks — I acknowledged the shortcoming\n\n\n============================================================\nSESSION: 81925542-1588-4cfc-8284-8adba71eb832\nDATE: Fri 2026-03-19+ (TUI session, 27 Tiny messages)\nSTATUS: NEEDS FULL READ\nNOTE: This is the MAIN agent session (not subagent). Has actual Tiny messages via TUI.\n============================================================\n\n============================================================\nSESSION: 36da5e41-d038-4c2e-87ad-3477fd17181d\nDATE: Fri 2026-03-20 (26 Tiny messages + system reminder)\nSTATUS: NEEDS FULL READ\nNOTE: System reminder at start (sprint check-in). TUI session with real Tiny messages.\n============================================================\n\n============================================================\nSESSION: 1cec01d5-0b1b-4a45-bcfa-a37c129aa58f\nDATE: Sat 2026-03-21 (5 Tiny messages, control-ui)\nSTATUS: NEEDS FULL READ\nNOTE: Session stuck issue re