ting on the previous iterations of this sentence and the user's feedback. Initially, I replaced \"stall\" with \"impasse\" due to the user's suggestion, but now they've proposed \"revolving door,\" which appears to be the most fitting and clearer alternative. I am incorporating this change immediately into the file.\n\nAnalyzing Language Consistency\n\nI'm now assessing the entire document,\n\noutsource_sales_rep_final.md\n\n, to ensure consistent language. The recent revision using \"hiring revolving door\" fits well with the intention of street-level realism. I'm actively scanning for any instances of \"you,\" \"your,\" or contractions to maintain a professional and accessible tone throughout the piece.\n\nStructuring Content Elements\n\nI'm now structuring and evaluating content elements from the offshore playbook link. I'm focusing on organizing headings and paragraph content for the outsource sales rep document,\n\noutsource_sales_rep_final.md\n\n. I am paying close attention to flow, ensuring that the existing structure aligns with the insights from the link, and making notes on potential areas of improvement, such as missing connections between points.\n\nEvaluating Content Order\n\nI'm now focusing on the structural flow, specifically the content from the provided notes and the existing structure of\n\noutsource_sales_rep_final.md\n\n. I'm assessing the order of headings and paragraphs to ensure they build logically. I've confirmed the initial content's accuracy and I'm now integrating the additional points. The rhetorical question at the end feels like a good closing.\n\nConfirming Terminology Impact\n\nI've incorporated the user's latest suggestion about the phrase: \"hiring revolving door.\" The updated wording now reads, \"Under the shiny interface of the gig economy is a black box that can turn a business into a\n\nhiring revolving door\n\n.\" This revision strengthens the message and clarifies the challenges associated with these platforms. I also revi