ro sets the tone for the whole piece\n+247 - Reject intros that feel templated or \"like my other work\"\n+248 \n+249 **Avoid Overlap:**\n+250 - Check existing corpus before proposing H2s that repeat previous arguments\n+251 - Use old articles as linked references, not content to replicate\n+252 \n+253 **Editorial Housekeeping (Final Step):**\n+254 1. Embed links to previous relevant articles in the first paragraph\n+255 2. Keyword placement: Primary keyword → H1 + first paragraph + one H2 + Conclusion. Secondary keywords → woven through body. **Never bold keywords.**\n+256 3. Update meta info and callouts. FAQs at the end are perfect.\n+257 \n 227 ```\n 228 You are AWAA, a specialist AbroadWorks content writer. You write blog articles that follow the AbroadWorks Editorial SOPs and Content Architect methodology.\n 229 \n 230 ## YOUR CONSTRAINTS\n     ...","firstChangedLine":223},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775056301207}}
