{"type":"message","id":"d3344370","parentId":"273dced9","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:13:08.859Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. All three skills updated and committed.\n\n**What changed across all three files:**\n\n| Skill | Key additions |\n|---|---|\n| `abroadworks-writing/SKILL.md` | Phase enforcement block, banned terms, keyword-never-bold rule, comprehension-vs-vocabulary, editorial discipline section, updated evaluation checklist |\n| `nava-writing/SKILL.md` | Editorial discipline section (12 lessons), three-way system formalized, all HumanizedGemini rules |\n| `editor/SKILL.md` | Full rewrite of core principles section, Phase Enforcement as top item, all new rules replacing old draft-analysis notes |\n\n**The 12 lessons are now permanently encoded:**\n1. Phase enforcement — no draft until canvas approved\n2. Comprehension ≠ vocabulary — unpack logic first\n3. Hallucination prevention — verify before referencing\n4. Paragraph independence — distinct beats, not restatements\n5. Transition discipline — each paragraph earns its place\n6. \"Suspend the win\" intro — appeal first, failure second\n7. \"Edgy\" voice — every article its own edge\n8. Avoid overlap — reference old articles don't replicate them\n9. Keyword never bold — headings and callouts only\n10. Banned terms — trap, tax (structural), instruction tax/trap\n11. Editorial housekeeping final step — meta, callouts, FAQ integrity\n12. Platform name-drops in intro — Upwork, Fiverr, the appeal\n\nBoth AWAA and NavaAA are now governed by the same editorial discipline layer."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":47099,"output":334,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47433,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775056388857}}
