s\n- [ ] Extracting readable text from HumanizedGemini.html (blocked by large inline script data)\n- [ ] Final review of transitions after update\n- [ ] Adding AbroadWorks article link to introduction\n- [ ] Adding primary/secondary keywords to headings and body text\n\n### Blocked\n- Large inline script data in line 3 of HTML (546.9KB) is interfering with text extraction\n- Python extraction script was truncated at 15000 characters\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Python-based extraction approach**: Used HTMLParser with script/style removal to clean content before extracting text\n- **Differentiation strategy for Admin burden articles**: Using \"Identity Black Market\" and \"Administrative Amnesia\" pivots to avoid reprinting \"founders doing too much\" arguments\n- **Contextual linking approach**: Link to existing proven concepts rather than re-explaining, spend word count on admin-specific friction points\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Complete extraction of HumanizedGemini.html content\n2. Analyze the editing decisions visible in the conversation\n3. Identify where user overrode GPT vs accepted suggestions vs manual edits\n4. Update editor skill based on learned principles\n5. Finalize FA5 section (appears truncated)\n6. Respond to Content Architect's question about final review of transitions\n7. Complete\n\n[Compaction summary truncated to fit budget]\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Goal\n- Pre-compaction memory flush: Store durable memories in memory/2026-04-01.md\n- Update editor skill (SKILL.md) with all 12 lessons from HumanizedGemini.html session\n- Determine whether to create separate `skills/editorial-discipline/` or merge into existing abroadworks-writing\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files (MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, AGENTS.md) as read-only — never overwrite\n- APPEND to existing memory/2026-04-01.md — do not overwrite\n- Use canonical 2026-04-01.md filename only (no timestamped variants)\n- Create memory/ directory i