nces → one flowing sentence with specifics (training manuals, performance reviews — concrete examples of what \"process\" actually means).\n+257 \n+258 6. **Closing calibration.** \"Strategic failure\" → \"strategic misstep\" in final pivot. Failure sounds like defeat; misstep keeps the door open for the solution.\n+259 \n+260 7. **Minimal FAQ changes.** Numerals cleaned up (\"nine out of nine\" → \"9 out of 10\"), formatting normalized.\n+261 \n+262 **Core philosophy:** Not rewriting — calibrating. Most changes are: more specific metaphors, removing abstraction, making vague claims concrete, swapping formulaic transitions for natural ones.\n+263 \n+264 **The through-line:** Original felt like someone explaining a concept. Final feels like someone who's seen it. That \"been there\" texture is what humanization actually is.\n+265 \n+266 ---\n+267 \n+268 ## 17:20 UTC — Editor Skill Updated and Committed\n+269 \n+270 Updated `skills/editor/SKILL.md` with all 12 lessons from HumanizedGemini.html session. Committed to git. Confirmed in previous message to Tiny.\n+271 \n+272 **Pending:** Nothing — editor skill updated, committed, reported. Awaiting Tiny's next direction (running Updated: Outsource Sales Rep through TinyQE).","firstChangedLine":234},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775057071213}}
