{"type":"message","id":"497326ad","parentId":"7751dfe2","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:26:39.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n**TinyQE Results — \"Updated: Outsource Sales Rep\"**\n\n---\n\n**Overall: 0.605 — Warning zone**\n\n---\n\n**Priority Queue (severity × weight):**\n\n**1. Readability (A2) — FAIL — severity 0.63**\nFKGL 12.6. Target for B2B blog content is 10.0. This is almost graduate-level reading. Sentences are too long and complex. Needs simpler structure throughout.\n\n**2. Proportionality (C3) — FAIL — severity 0.67**\nEvidence (weak) can't support the claims being made (extraordinary). The article says things like \"9 out of 10 sales teams will miss their goals\" and \"61% of B2B buyers purchase solutions for problems they didn't know they had\" — big stats, but the evidence backing them is thin. Either cite stronger sources or dial the claim language back.\n\n**3. Logical Flow (B2) — FAIL — severity 0.85**\nFragmented connections between sentences. Many paragraphs read as lists of assertions rather than connected argument. The \"bridge protocol\" rule (transition words on every paragraph lead) is being violated throughout. This is the most actionable fix — it's mechanical, not conceptual.\n\n**4. Thesis Clarity (B1) — Warning**\nMultiple competing thesis candidates detected. The opening paragraph makes several large claims (performance gap, $15T market, 40% CAC increase) without landing on one clear primary thesis. The reader doesn't know what the article is *about* until partway through.\n\n**5. Linguistic Integrity (A1) — Warning (55 errors)**\nMechanical errors: spacing after commas (\"7,0\" instead of \"7, 0\"), missing spaces after periods (\"f.a\", \"o.c\"). Easy fixes but pervasive — likely from copy-pasting from different sources.\n\n**6. Argumentative Rigor (C2) — Warning**\nAppeal-to-authority fallacy detected. The article cites \"research indicates\" and unnamed studies without linking to the actual source. Readers can't verify.\n\n---\n\n**What's working:**\n- **Authorial Voice (D1):** 0.94 — strong, consistent voice\n- **Emotional Calibration (D3):** 1.0 — tone appropriate for subject\n- **Structural Completeness (B3):** 0.67 — has context, evidence, counterargument, resolution\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** The readability and flow issues are the fastest fixes — they're mechanical. The proportionality problem (big claims, thin evidence) is the harder editorial issue. That's a rewrite problem, not a tweak problem."}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":38008,"output":939,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38947,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775057199030}}
