{"type":"message","id":"96340639","parentId":"d44c4442","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:43:23.371Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_2fd31aa8-ee93-443f-b769-9c6e92aa411f","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li002_final.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":40,"aggregated":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li002_final.md","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775058203366}}
{"type":"message","id":"870c0fd2","parentId":"96340639","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:43:27.132Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_c97b33ef-fe9f-43c7-90cd-b3274afa92e0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li002_final.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27142,"output":76,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27218,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775058207132}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f8447e3","parentId":"870c0fd2","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:43:27.159Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_c97b33ef-fe9f-43c7-90cd-b3274afa92e0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\" (Final Draft — Posted Mar 24, 2026)\n\n**Hook:** Census argument — LTC patients are cognitively impaired; the 13-week travel cycle is uniquely harmful to this population, not just inconvenient\n\n**Post:**\n---\nIn long-term care, the patient at the end of the hall has been disoriented three times this year.\n\nThe same routine. A different face. A different name.\n\nIn hospitals, travel nurses fill shifts. In long-term care, they fill something more fragile: the patient's sense of safety in a world they can no longer navigate alone.\n\nLong-term care residents are older, sicker, and more cognitively impaired than any acute care population. They cannot adapt to new faces every 13 weeks. Research shows that repeated staff turnover in dementia units correlates with measurable clinical deterioration — not inconvenience, deterioration.\n\nThe 13-week cycle was built for hospitals. It was never built for memory care.\n\nThe alternative isn't a better travel agency. It's a different model entirely.\n\nInternational nurses on EB-3 green card pathways commit to three-year terms — 6,000 hours of embedded, relational care. They learn the unit. They learn the patients. They stay.\n\nFacilities running this math see the numbers clearly: replacing a single travel nurse with a permanent hire saves an average of $79,100 per year. Over a facility running 50 travel roles, that compounds into something that changes the economics of the entire building.\n\nThat's the LTC staffing model nobody is talking about.\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment — permanent international placements for facilities that need stability, not cycles.\n---\n\n**Posted:** 2026-03-24 ~21:00 UTC\n**Platform:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment LinkedIn Page\n**Status:** ✅ LIVE\n**Post URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7442315133936254976?actorCompanyId=67170741"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"# LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\" (Final Draft — Posted Mar 24, 2026)\n\n**Hook:** Census argument — LTC patients are cognitively impaired; the 13-week travel cycle is uniquely harmful to this population, not just inconvenient\n\n**Post:**\n---\nIn long-term care, the patient at the end of the hall has been disoriented three times this year.\n\nThe same routine. A different face. A different name.\n\nIn hospitals, travel nurses fill shifts. In long-term care, they fill something more fragile: the patient's sense of safety in a world they can no longer navigate alone.\n\nLong-term care residents are older, sicker, and more cognitively impaired than any acute care population. They cannot adapt to new faces every 13 weeks. Research shows that repeated staff turnover in dementia units correlates with measurable clinical deterioration — not inconvenience, deterioration.\n\nThe 13-week cycle was built for hospitals. It was never built for memory care.\n\nThe alternative isn't a better travel agency. It's a different model entirely.\n\nInternational nurses on EB-3 green card pathways commit to three-year terms — 6,000 hours of embedded, relational care. They learn the unit. They learn the patients. They stay.\n\nFacilities running this math see the numbers clearly: replacing a single travel nurse with a permanent hire saves an average of $79,100 per year. Over a facility running 50 travel roles, that compounds into something that changes the economics of the entire building.\n\nThat's the LTC staffing model nobody is talking about.\n\nNava Healthcare Recruitment — permanent international placements for facilities that need stability, not cycles.\n---\n\n**Posted:** 2026-03-24 ~21:00 UTC\n**Platform:** Nava Healthcare Recruitment LinkedIn Page\n**Status:** ✅ LIVE\n**Post URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7442315133936254976?actorCompanyId=67170741","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775058207154}}
{"type":"message","id":"dded7d0b","parentId":"5f8447e3","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:43:39.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's **LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\"** — posted **Mar 24**. You did post it. It's in our corpus as `li002_final.md`.\n\nCheck your LinkedIn page if you don't believe yourself: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7442315133936254976?actorCompanyId=67170741\n\n(Posted 21:00 UTC Mar 24, from the Nava Healthcare Recruitment page.)\n\nYou were likely tired or it was a long session — easy to forget six days ago.\n\nNow — your new blog post today (April 1): what's the URL so I can read it and build the LinkedIn post from it?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27600,"output":397,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27997,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775058219021}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e838479","parentId":"dded7d0b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:45:56.162Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 17:45 GMT+2] No, I meant I want to create posts centered around that 13 week post. Let's begin. Tell me the concept of my next LI concept (also, start taking notes. I need you to learn from this process.)"}],"timestamp":1775058356134}}
{"type":"message","id":"b670112d","parentId":"1e838479","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:46:16.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nNoted. Starting the process log now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d019f43a-93ab-4e41-b572-6bd9c9d7e378","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/process-logs && cat > /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/process-logs/2026-04-01-content-sprint.md << 'EOF'\n# Content Sprint — 2026-04-01\n\n## Topic Cluster\n**Core post:** LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\" (posted Mar 24)\n**Theme:** Travel nurse 13-week cycles are uniquely harmful to LTC/memory care patients; EB-3 permanent placement as the structural fix.\n\n## Goal\nQueue 6 posts centered on the 13-week/LTC staffing cluster.\n\n## Process Notes\n- Tiny wants me to LEARN from this process — capture editorial decisions, not just outputs\n- Each concept decision = note why Tiny chose it / rejected alternatives\n- Each draft = note what changed from AI draft to final and WHY\n\n## Post Queue (TBD — concepts to define)\n- LI003: TBD\n- LI004: TBD\n- LI005: TBD\n- LI006: TBD\n- X versions: TBD\n\n## Concept Decisions\nEOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27873,"output":581,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28454,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775058376600}}
