{"type":"message","id":"0b3732c6","parentId":"2aaa4ea4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:46:40.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the concept directions for the 13-week cluster — pick what to pressure-test:\n\n**A. The HR Manager's Hidden Work** — Every 13 weeks, your unit manager re-onboards a stranger. The credentialing, the orientation, the \"where's the medication cart.\" That's invisible labor nobody counts. The angle: your best managers are burning out on rotational churn, not patient care.\n\n**B. The Full Cost Angles** — We have the $79,100 savings figure. But the real cascade: agency fee + overtime premiums + PRN spreads + orientation hours + patient outcome decline in memory care. Run the full number, not the headline.\n\n**C. The International Nurse's Side** — EB-3 nurses commit 3 years, get green cards, build careers. The other side of the permanence argument. Why they prefer this model. What embedded, relational care actually looks like from the nurse's perspective.\n\n**D. The Compliance/Risk Angle** — Travel nurses working across multiple facilities = credentialing gaps, infection control exposure, credential verification failures. Risk that never shows up in the agency contract fine print.\n\n**E. The Parallel Track CTA** — LI002 made the EB-3 case. This one targets facilities already running travel nurses AND considering international: how to run both tracks without them cannibalising each other.\n\n**F. The Market Timing** — April 2026 visa bulletin. EB-3 ROW dates filing = current. The window is open now. Facilities sitting on outdated assumptions are leaving their staffing plans unspoken for.\n\nWhich do you want to start with? And should we go deeper on A or B first — the human/operational pain or the financial math?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":28165,"output":730,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28895,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775058400717}}
