lCall]\n- Tool result (exec): ## Nava Post Status (as of Mar 24)\n\n- **Post 001 (LI):** ✅ \"The Incentive Trap\" — posted Mar 20\n- **Post 001 (X):** ⏳ Draft delivered Mar 22, awaiting review (fee alignment topic)\n- **Post 002 (LI):** Concept agreed — LTC + NurseSphere (root cause: international pipeline). Hook not yet decided. Draft never written.\n- **Post 002 (X):** Not started\n- **Writing lesson:** Pending (needs Tiny walkthrough of how LI Post 001 was actually written)\n\n## Workflow Rule (hard)\nConcept → review → draft → finalize. Review step is NOT skippable. Do not draft subsequent posts until previous post is reviewed an...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): total 12444\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv     4096 Mar 28 09:24 .\ndrwxrwxr-x 10 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv     4096 Mar 25 14:49 ..\n-rw-rw-r--  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv    32536 Mar 27 12:47 TINYQE_RESEARCH_GEMINI_NAVA.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv     4002 Mar 27 13:07 TINYQE_RUBRIC_DRAFT.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv     7739 Mar 19 10:54 archived_draft_001_v1_ai.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv     3104 Mar 24 22:34 gemini-ltc-research-2026-03-24.md\n-rwxrwxr-x  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv 12564064 Mar 24 13:05 gemini-nursesphere-deep-research.html\n-rw-rw-r--  1 tiny4lurv tiny4lurv    ...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): # LI026 — EB-3 vs TN: The False Choice (LinkedIn Post)\n\n---\n\nYour travel nurse invoice arrives every 13 weeks.\n\nMeanwhile, someone in your HR meeting is still arguing about EB-3 versus TN like you can only pick one.\n\nStop.\n\nEB-3 is a permanence play. Three years minimum before the math works. TN is a speed play. Two to six months before your candidate is on unit. The moment you treat those as competitors, you've already lost the staffing conversation you should be having.\n\nHere is what the comparison actually looks like when you run it honestly.\n\nTN all-in runs $7,000 to $15,000 per candidate....\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): # X029 — \"EB-3 or TN: The Wrong Question\"\n\n## The Post\n\nEB-3 or TN?\n\nThat's the wrong question.\n\nThe EB-3 pathway is permanent residency. Slower, costlier upfront. The nurse arrives as a green card holder.\n\nThe TN pathway is temporary work authorization. Faster, cheaper. Restricted to Canadian and Mexican nationals under USMCA.\n\nThese are not two options on the same menu. They answer different strategic questions.\n\nThe facilities getting this right are running both.\n\nOne pipeline for positions to fill in the next six months. One pipeline for the permanent staffing base built over three years.\n...\n- Assistant: Yes, I can see the queue from the Mar 28 session. Here's what's in drafts:\n\n| File | Topic | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| `li026_linkedin.md` | EB-3 vs TN parallel track | ✅ Final — needs review |\n| `x029_eb3_vs_tn.md` | X version of above | ✅ Ready |\n| `li026_v2.md` | Blog post (15KB) — foundation for LI026 | ✅ Exists |\n| `li027_nursesphere_introduction.md` | NurseSphere intro | Draft |\n| `li028_13_week_problem.md` | 13-week problem | Draft |\n| `li029_eb3_vs_tn.md` | EB-3 vs TN (detailed) | Draft |\n| `li030_parallel_track.md` | Parallel track strategy | Draft |\n| `li031_nursesphere_recruitment.md...\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 17:43 GMT+2] I have posted a new blog post, check the live Nava blog. \n\nCritical question: There is a post on LinkedIn, it starts with this:\nIn long-term care, the patient at the end of the hall has been disoriented three times this year.\n\nThe same routine. A different face. A different name.\n\nDid you post this?? I don't remember doing this.\n- Assistant: I did not post anything — no LinkedIn access beyond reading. Let me check the Nava LinkedIn page and match it against our corpus.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/li002_final.md\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): # LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\" (Final Draft — Posted Mar 24, 2026)\n\n**Hook:** Census argument — LTC patients are cognitively impaired; the 13-week travel cycle is uniquely harmful to this population, not just inconvenient\n\n**Post:**\n---\nIn long-term care, the patient at the end of the hall has been disoriented three times this year.\n\nThe same routine. A different face. A different name.\n\nIn hospitals, travel nurses fill shifts. In long-term care, they fill something more fragile: the patient's sense of safety in a world they can no longer navigate alone.\n\nLong-term care residents are o...\n- Assistant: That's **LI002 — \"The 13-Week Problem in LTC\"** — posted **Mar 24**. You did post it. It's in our corpus as `li002_final.md`.\n\nCheck your LinkedIn page if you don't believe yourself: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7442315133936254976?actorCompanyId=67170741\n\n(Posted 21:00 UTC Mar 24, from the Nava Healthcare Recruitment page.)\n\nYou were likely tired or it was a long session — easy to forget six days ago.\n\nNow — your new blog post today (April 1): what's the URL so I can read it and build the LinkedIn post from it?\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 17:45 GMT+2] No, I meant I want to create posts centered around that 13 week post. Let's begin. Tell me the concept of my next LI concept (also, start taking notes. I need you to learn from this process.)\n- Assistant: Noted. Starting the process log now.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (exec): (no output)\n- Assistant: Here are the concept directions for the 13-week cluster — pick what to pressure-test:\n\n**A. The HR Manager's Hidden Work** — Every 13 weeks, your unit manager re-onboards a stranger. The credentialing, the orientation, the \"where's the medication cart.\" That's invisible labor nobody counts. The angle: your best managers are burning out on rotational churn, not patient care.\n\n**B. The Full Cost Angles** — We have the $79,100 savings figure. But the real cascade: agency fee + overtime premiums + PRN spreads + orientation hours + patient outcome decline in memory care. Run the full number, not th...","firstKeptEntryId":"54f36e40","tokensBefore":51555,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
