{"type":"message","id":"5343963c","parentId":"01335709","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:15.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_1e472578-f879-45a3-af9a-998f84094172","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TinyQE Assessment — Generic\n\nOverall: Needs Work. Content shows promise but requires significant improvement.\n\nTop 3 Priorities:\n1. Linguistic Integrity (severity: high | weight: 8%) — 2 mechanical errors detected. Highest priority: missing space after period\n   → Address errors in order: missing space after period, missing space after period\n2. Thesis Clarity (severity: high | weight: 8%) — No clear thesis detected.\n   → State your central claim clearly in the opening paragraph.\n3. Structural Completeness (severity: high | weight: 8%) — Structure is incomplete. Missing: CLAIM, EVIDENCE, RESOLUTION.\n   → Restructure to include: claim → setup → evidence → complication → resolution.\n\nNote: Scores are diagnostic, not judgmental. Focus on the priority queue for actionable feedback.\nFormat detected: Generic (confidence: 50%)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1552,"aggregated":"TinyQE Assessment — Generic\n\nOverall: Needs Work. Content shows promise but requires significant improvement.\n\nTop 3 Priorities:\n1. Linguistic Integrity (severity: high | weight: 8%) — 2 mechanical errors detected. Highest priority: missing space after period\n   → Address errors in order: missing space after period, missing space after period\n2. Thesis Clarity (severity: high | weight: 8%) — No clear thesis detected.\n   → State your central claim clearly in the opening paragraph.\n3. Structural Completeness (severity: high | weight: 8%) — Structure is incomplete. Missing: CLAIM, EVIDENCE, RESOLUTION.\n   → Restructure to include: claim → setup → evidence → complication → resolution.\n\nNote: Scores are diagnostic, not judgmental. Focus on the priority queue for actionable feedback.\nFormat detected: Generic (confidence: 50%)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775059515826}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba9581ff","parentId":"5343963c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:28.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Same result — the Generic profile is overriding everything. Let me dig into the actual errors the tool is detecting:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e4063021-51d6-41f9-bd4c-88071c0cc1ec","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/linguistic_integrity.py"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":46769,"output":169,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775059528006}}
{"type":"message","id":"c26fa97d","parentId":"ba9581ff","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:28.030Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_e4063021-51d6-41f9-bd4c-88071c0cc1ec","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nLinguistic Integrity Analyzer (A1)\nDetects mechanical errors: spelling, punctuation, subject-verb agreement, article usage.\nOutputs score 0.0-1.0 where 1.0 = no errors.\n\"\"\"\nimport re\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Tuple\n\n# High-frequency error patterns (rule-based, zero false positives where possible)\nSPELLING_ERRORS = {\n    r\"\\breciev\\w*\": \"receive\",\n    r\"\\bdefinately\\b\": \"definitely\",\n    r\"\\boccured\\b\": \"occurred\",\n    r\"\\buntill\\b\": \"until\",\n    r\"\\bteh\\b\": \"the\",\n    r\"\\badn\\b\": \"and\",\n    r\"\\btha\\b\": \"the\",\n    r\"\\broung\\b\": \"wrong\",\n}\n\nPUNCTUATION_ERRORS = [\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\,[^\\s]\", \"missing space after comma\"),\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]\", \"missing space after period\"),\n    (r\"\\s+[,.;:]\", \"space before punctuation\"),\n    (r\"[.!?]{2,}\", \"excessive punctuation\"),\n]\n\nARTICLE_ERRORS = [\n    (r\"\\ban\\s+[aeiou]\", \"use 'a' before consonant sound\"),\n    (r\"\\ba\\s+[aeiou]\", \"use 'an' before vowel sound\"),\n]\n\nSUBJECT_VERB_PATTERNS = [\n    # He go -> He goes\n    (r\"\\b(he|she|it)\\s+(\\w+)(?!s\\b)\", \"subject-verb agreement: third person singular missing -s\"),\n    # They goes -> They go\n    (r\"\\b(they|we|you)\\s+(\\w+)s\\b\", \"subject-verb agreement: plural subject with singular verb\"),\n]\n\ndef apply_rules(text: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Apply rule-based detectors. Returns list of error dicts.\"\"\"\n    errors = []\n\n    # Spelling\n    for pattern, correction in SPELLING_ERRORS.items():\n        for match in re.finditer(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE):\n            errors.append({\n                \"type\": \"spelling\",\n                \"passage\": match.group(),\n                \"location\": f\"char {match.start()}-{match.end()}\",\n                \"expected\": correction,\n                \"message\": f\"Possible spelling error: '{match.group()}' -> '{correction}'\",\n                \"severity\": \"error\"\n            })\n\n    # Punctuation\n    for pattern, message in PUNCTUATION_ERRORS:\n        for match in re.finditer(pattern, text):\n            errors.append({\n                \"type\": \"punctuation\",\n                \"passage\": match.group(),\n                \"location\": f\"char {match.start()}-{match.end()}\",\n                \"message\": message,\n                \"severity\": \"error\"\n            })\n\n    # Articles\n    for pattern, message in ARTICLE_ERRORS:\n        for match in re.finditer(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE):\n            errors.append({\n                \"type\": \"article\",\n                \"passage\": match.group(),\n                \"location\": f\"char {match.start()}-{match.end()}\",\n                \"message\": message,\n                \"severity\": \"warning\"\n            })\n\n    # Subject-verb (lightweight)\n    for pattern, message in SUBJECT_VERB_PATTERNS:\n        for match in re.finditer(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE):\n            errors.append({\n                \"type\": \"subject_verb\",\n                \"passage\": match.group(),\n                \"location\": f\"char {match.start()}-{match.end()}\",\n                \"message\": message,\n                \"severity\": \"warning\"\n            })\n\n    return errors\n\ndef call_ollama_for_grammar(text: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Optional: Use Ollama for contextual grammar only if rule-based found >= 2 errors\n    or if text is short (< 50 words) to avoid overuse.\n    Returns list of error dicts from model.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Heuristic: only call model if we already see multiple errors or very short text\n    words = len(text.split())\n    if words > 100:\n        return []  # Skip for long texts to save tokens/cost\n\n    prompt = f\"\"\"You are a grammar checker. Find ONLY grammatical errors in this text:\nSubject-verb agreement, article usage, pronoun case, verb tense consistency.\nDo NOT flag style, word choice, or readability.\nIf no errors, respond with exactly: NO_ERRORS\n\nText:\n\\\"\\\"\\\"{text}\\\"\\\"\\\"\"\"\"\n\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"ollama\", \"run\", \"gemma3:27b-cloud\", prompt],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=15\n        )\n        output = result.stdout.strip()\n        if output == \"NO_ERRORS\":\n            return []\n\n        # Parse model output - expect one error per line\n        errors = []\n        for line in output.split('\\n'):\n            if line.strip():\n                errors.append({\n                    \"type\": \"contextual_grammar\",\n                    \"passage\": line.strip(),  # Simplified\n                    \"location\": \"contextual\",\n                    \"message\": line.strip(),\n                    \"severity\": \"error\"\n                })\n        return errors\n    except Exception as e:\n        # Fail open: if Ollama unavailable, don't block\n        print(f\"[WARN] Ollama grammar check failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return []\n\ndef analyze(text: str, format_hint: str = \"generic\", format_profile: Dict = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Main entry point.\n    Returns dict with score, verdict, confidence, evidence, interpretation, recommendation.\n    \"\"\"\n    rule_errors = apply_rules(text)\n    # Only call Ollama if we need more depth or text is short\n    ai_errors = call_ollama_for_grammar(text) if len(rule_errors) < 3 or len(text.split()) < 50 else []\n\n    all_errors = rule_errors + ai_errors\n    error_count = len(all_errors)\n\n    # Scoring: logarithmic penalty to avoid 0 score for long texts with few errors\n    word_count = max(len(text.split()), 1)\n    # Base score: 1.0 minus penalty that grows with error density\n    error_density = error_count / word_count\n    # At 1 error per 10 words -> score ~0.6; 1 per 5 -> ~0.3; 1 per 20 -> ~0.8\n    score = max(0.0, 1.0 - (error_density * 5.0))\n\n    # Clamp and round\n    score = round(min(1.0, max(0.0, score)), 3)\n\n    # Verdict thresholds\n    if score >= 0.8:\n        verdict = \"pass\"\n    elif score >= 0.5:\n        verdict = \"warning\"\n    else:\n        verdict = \"fail\"\n\n    # Confidence: high for rule-based, lower for AI-assisted\n    confidence = 0.95 if len(ai_errors) == 0 else 0.75\n\n    # Build evidence list for output\n    evidence = []\n    for err in all_errors[:5]:  # Limit output\n        evidence.append({\n            \"passage\": err.get(\"passage\", \"\"),\n            \"location\": err.get(\"location\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"signal\": err.get(\"message\", \"\"),\n            \"severity\": err.get(\"severity\", \"error\")\n        })\n\n    # Interpretation and recommendation\n    if error_count == 0:\n        interpretation = \"No mechanical errors detected.\"\n        recommendation = \"Text is mechanically sound.\"\n    elif error_count == 1:\n        interpretation = f\"One mechanical error detected: {all_errors[0]['message']}\"\n        recommendation = f\"Fix: {all_errors[0].get('expected', 'review')}\"\n    else:\n        interpretation = f\"{error_count} mechanical errors detected. Highest priority: {all_errors[0]['message']}\"\n        recommendation = \"Address errors in order: \" + \", \".join(\n            [e['message'] for e in all_errors[:3]]\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"dimension\": \"A1\",\n        \"dimension_name\": \"Linguistic Integrity\",\n        \"score\": score,\n        \"verdict\": verdict,\n        \"confidence\": confidence,\n        \"evidence\": evidence,\n        \"interpretation\": interpretation,\n        \"recommendation\": recommendation\n    }\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Allow testing from command line\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        text = \" \".join(sys.argv[1:])\n    else:\n        text = sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    result = analyze(text)\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775059528025}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdc601ae","parentId":"c26fa97d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:05:49.180Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nFound the bug — the linguistic integrity analyzer has a regex `[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]` that's a false positive engine. It's triggering on every abbreviation like `Dr.`, `U.S.`, `EB-3.`, etc. — not actual spacing errors. Let me find the actual false positive:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e5f703ba-b938-48c8-9cae-12a6ee36f37c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe && python3 -c \"\nimport re\ntext = open('/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md').read()\n# The buggy pattern\nfor m in re.finditer(r'[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]', text):\n    print(f'pos {m.start()}: {repr(text[max(0,m.start()-5):m.end()+5])}')\n\" 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":44669,"output":682,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45351,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775059549179}}
