{"type":"message","id":"b34bc0dc","parentId":"3383bf00","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:06:58.952Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The TinyQE alerts are all false positives — the regex fires on periods before newlines and asterisks. V3 has no real mechanical errors. Let me do a final editorial pass, verify the URL is clean, and save to Downloads.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d15141f7-e42f-40c7-b454-d1be91dec978","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\ntext = open('/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md').read()\n# Check for actual spacing errors (period followed by letter with no space)\nimport re\n# Real spacing error: period then letter with no space, NOT newline/asterisk/quote\nreal_errors = []\nfor m in re.finditer(r'\\.([a-zA-Z])', text):\n    next_char = m.string[m.end()] if m.end() < len(text) else ''\n    # Allow if followed by newline or asterisk or blockquote marker\n    if next_char not in ('\\n', '*', '>', ' '):\n        real_errors.append((m.start(), repr(m.group()), repr(next_char)))\nprint(f'Real spacing errors: {len(real_errors)}')\nfor pos, g, n in real_errors[:5]:\n    print(f'  {pos}: {g} followed by {n}')\n# Check URLs\nurls = re.findall(r'https?://[^\\s\\)]+', text)\nprint(f'URLs found: {len(urls)}')\nfor u in urls:\n    print(f'  {u}')\n\"\n"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":45400,"output":663,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46063,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775059618952}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fb7d537","parentId":"b34bc0dc","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:06:59.010Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d15141f7-e42f-40c7-b454-d1be91dec978","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real spacing errors: 4\n  1146: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  4176: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  8024: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  10359: '.c' followed by 'o'\nURLs found: 4\n  https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/\n  https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/\n  https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/\n  https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":43,"aggregated":"Real spacing errors: 4\n  1146: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  4176: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  8024: '.c' followed by 'o'\n  10359: '.c' followed by 'o'\nURLs found: 4\n  https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/\n  https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/\n  https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/\n  https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775059619004}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef63da97","parentId":"0fb7d537","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:07:20.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Those 4 \"real\" errors are periods inside URLs (`navahc.com/the`). I can fix those by converting to markdown link format. Let me do that and save the final to Downloads:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_7bb30c6e-e404-4a33-9584-b81a6a4f9d70","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport re\n\ntext = open('/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md').read()\n\n# Convert bare URLs in parentheses to markdown links\n# Pattern: (https://...) -> [<text>](https://...)\n# We want to keep the display text clean\n\n# Fix: [Treating them as equivalents is like comparing a mortgage to a hotel reservation](https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/)\n# Already clean, just check\n\n# Fix URLs inside parentheses: (https://...) -> markdown link\ndef url_to_md_link(match):\n    url = match.group(1)\n    # Extract a short label from URL\n    label = url.split('/')[-1].replace('-', ' ').title()\n    return f'[{label}]({url})'\n\n# Find URLs not already in markdown format\ndef fix_urls_in_parens(text):\n    # Match (https://.../) where the parentheses enclose ONLY the URL\n    def replacer(m):\n        url = m.group(1)\n        label = url.split('/')[-1].replace('-', ' ').title() or url\n        return f'[{label}]({url})'\n    return re.sub(r'\\(https://([^)\\s]+)\\)', replacer, text)\n\ntext = fix_urls_in_parens(text)\n\n# Now find remaining bare URLs and convert\n# Pattern: [text](url) is already markdown, we need to handle any remaining bare URLs\n# Fix: The <url> pattern where it's inline\ndef fix_inline_urls(text):\n    # Already markdown links - just clean up the URL periods\n    return text\n\nprint(\"URLs after fix:\")\nfor m in re.findall(r'https?://[^\\s\\)]+', text):\n    print(f\"  {m}\")\n\nopen('/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md', 'w').write(text)\nprint(\"Done\")\nEOF"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":45882,"output":740,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46622,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775059640674}}
