{"type":"message","id":"46ba24d6","parentId":"f0078bab","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:08:58.859Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now copy to Downloads:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e2d18fcc-d278-42ab-9e79-7ebee73e4066","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp \"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md\" \"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Visa Pathway Comparison v3.md\"\necho \"Copied\"\n# Verify URLs are clean\npython3 -c \"\nimport re\ntext = open('/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/rag/drafts/visa_pathway/v3_merged.md').read()\n# Check for malformed links\nbad = re.findall(r'\\[.*\\]\\[.*\\]\\(.*\\)', text)\nprint(f'Malformed links: {len(bad)}')\n# Check spacing errors (period-letter without space, excluding URLs and valid cases)\nerrors = []\nfor m in re.finditer(r'\\.([a-zA-Z])', text):\n    ctx = text[max(0,m.start()-20):m.end()+20]\n    # Skip if in a URL\n    if 'http' in ctx or 'navahc' in ctx.lower():\n        continue\n    errors.append(ctx)\nprint(f'Potential spacing errors (excl URLs): {len(errors)}')\nfor e in errors[:3]:\n    print(f'  {repr(e)}')\n# Verify all markdown links format\nlinks = re.findall(r'\\[([^\\]]+)\\]\\((https?://[^\\)]+)\\)', text)\nprint(f'Clean markdown links: {len(links)}')\nfor label, url in links:\n    print(f'  [{label}]({url})')\n\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":47208,"output":368,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775059738859}}
{"type":"message","id":"03b5195c","parentId":"46ba24d6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:08:58.930Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_e2d18fcc-d278-42ab-9e79-7ebee73e4066","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Copied\nMalformed links: 0\nPotential spacing errors (excl URLs): 0\nClean markdown links: 4\n  [Treating them as equivalents is like comparing a mortgage to a hotel reservation](https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/)\n  [easily reaches $200,000 to $400,000](https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/)\n  [Healthcare Workforce Resilience Act](https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/)\n  [Facilities that have made the three-year commitment and stayed the course](https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"Copied\nMalformed links: 0\nPotential spacing errors (excl URLs): 0\nClean markdown links: 4\n  [Treating them as equivalents is like comparing a mortgage to a hotel reservation](https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/)\n  [easily reaches $200,000 to $400,000](https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/)\n  [Healthcare Workforce Resilience Act](https://navahc.com/fix-your-flexible-staffing-model-in-healthcare/)\n  [Facilities that have made the three-year commitment and stayed the course](https://navahc.com/the-anatomy-of-a-clinician-turnover/)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775059738922}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba5646f7","parentId":"03b5195c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:09:15.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nNow save notes and let Tiny know:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_0dc8caa3-a0cf-42e4-a12b-1c563dcb052c","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-01.md","old_string":"**Awaiting from Tiny:**\n1. URL of blog post he just published (April 1)\n2. Decision: review/post existing LI26 + X18 drafts, or build new posts from the newly published article?\n3. His answer on whether the \"Visa Pathway\" article was the one he just published","new_string":"**Apr 1, 17:56 UTC — Visa Pathway Article (continued)**\n- Tiny had two ODT versions of \"Visa Pathway Comparison\" article\n- He wants me to: merge into new improved version, run NavaAA passes + TinyQE, save to Downloads\n- SoT: found in Downloads as `Healthcare Visa Pathways_ EB-3 vs. TN.md` (257 lines)\n- Tiny noted: in-text links only (no URL footer list)\n\n**Process:**\n- V2 as base (better rhythm, tighter narrative)\n- Grafted V1's 2026 Forecast section (time-sensitive visa bulletin intel)\n- Stripped all URL footer lists → markdown in-text links\n- Applied Nava voice rules throughout\n\n**Output:** `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Visa Pathway Comparison v3.md`\n- 4 clean markdown links (in-text)\n- 0 malformed links, 0 spacing errors\n- No URL footer\n\n**TinyQE findings (for Tiny's tool log):**\n- TinyQE linguistic_integrity analyzer has BUG: regex `[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]` false positives on periods before newlines/blockquotes\n- All \"missing space after period\" alerts = false positives (4 instances all inside URLs)\n- No actual mechanical errors in v3_merged.md\n- Blog format profile doesn't exist → TinyQE scores identically to Generic\n\n**TinyQE improvement backlog:**\n- Create `config/format_profiles/blog.json` format profile\n- Fix linguistic_integrity regex to exclude periods before `\\n`, `*`, `>`\n-