{"type":"message","id":"ebfc631e","parentId":"83cf5519","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:26:33.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Understood. TinyQE currently lacks a blog format profile — it's falling back to Generic scoring, which explains why the scores are identical across runs and don't reflect long-form blog expectations.\n\n**What needs to be done for TinyQE blog readiness:**\n\n1. **Create `config/format_profiles/blog.json`** — define weights for the 12 dimensions specific to long-form blog content (different from LinkedIn/X)\n2. **Fix the linguistic_integrity regex bug** — exclude periods before newlines and markdown markers to stop false positives on URLs and clean formatting\n3. **Optionally add blog-specific dimension tuning** — e.g., adjust Evidence Quality and Logical Flow expectations for essay-style vs social-post formats\n\nI'll handle this now — first checking if the blog profile exists, then creating it if not, and fixing the regex.\n\nLet me start by examining the current TinyQE structure:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_2a29bfc8-e790-45a9-95a2-cc17de44c770","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/config/format_profiles/"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"nemotron-3-super:cloud","usage":{"input":48519,"output":233,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48752,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775060793316}}
