{"type":"message","id":"a94bcd47","parentId":"ba2e00a7","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:27:20.534Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah! There it is. The matches are:\n- `c.c` from `navahc.com` — period between two letters\n- `y.*` from `urgency.** If` — period, newline, then `*` (markdown for bold)\n- `n.*` from `horizon.** EB-3` — same pattern\n- `e.\"` from a period followed by a quote\n\nSo the bug is real — the regex `[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]` matches:\n1. Period between two letters (in URLs) → false positive\n2. Period, newline, then non-whitespace (like `*` or `\"`) → also flagged as missing space, but this is actually correct markdown formatting\n\nFor case 1 (URLs): definitely a false positive — we should exclude periods that are part of domain names or paths.\nFor case 2 (markdown): debatable — but in markdown, a period before a newline followed by `*` (bold) or `\"` (quote) is actually correct syntax. The space after the period is implied by the line break.\n\nLet me fix the regex to be smarter:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_1c3e917e-28cb-41b8-a2fb-9f82521c9d92","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"PUNCTUATION_ERRORS = [\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\,[^\\s]\", \"missing space after comma\"),\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\.(?!\\s*[A-Za-z])[^\\s]\", \"missing space after period\"),\n    (r\"\\s+[,.;:]\", \"space before punctuation\"),\n    (r\"[.!?]{2,}\", \"excessive punctuation\"),\n]","old_string":"PUNCTUATION_ERRORS = [\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\,[^\\s]\", \"missing space after comma\"),\n    (r\"[^\\s]\\.[^\\s]\", \"missing space after period\"),\n    (r\"\\s+[,.;:]\", \"space before punctuation\"),\n    (r\"[.!?]{2,}\", \"excessive punctuation\"),\n]","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/linguistic_integrity.py"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"nemotron-3-super:cloud","usage":{"input":51882,"output":478,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52360,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"