{"type":"message","id":"95264b3c","parentId":"1632bfc4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:33:30.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll evaluate v3 against the editor skill principles and list any violations before fixing them. Let me go through the skill systematically.\n\n**EDITOR SKILL EVALUATION — VISA PATHWAY COMPARISON V3**\n\nI'll check each constraint from the editor skill and note violations.\n\n### HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\n#### Structure\n1. **2x4-6 Rule**: Each H3 section contains 2 paragraphs, each with 4-6 sentences.\n   - **VIOLATION**: No H3 sections exist — this is a Statement of Trade, not a blog article with H2→H3 hierarchy. The structure is linear prose. *Acceptable for SoT format, but violates the literal rule.*\n\n2. **H2 Introductions**: Every H2 heading must have a contextualizing paragraph immediately beneath it before H3s begin.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ All H2 sections have contextualizing intros (e.g., \"You're Asking the Wrong Question\", \"The Math You've Never Seen Laid Out\")\n\n3. **Blockquote Callouts**: Each H2 section ends with a blockquote axiom.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ All four H2 sections end with blockquotes\n\n#### Formatting\n1. **No Bold in Body**: Bold is for headings (H1, H2, H3) and blockquote callouts only.\n   - **VIOLATION**: Line 5 has bold in body: \"**The right visa pathway is the one that matches your actual staffing situation.**\" — this is a section-intro pivot, not a heading. *Borderline violation.*\n\n2. **No Em-Dashes**: Never use `—` or `–`.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Zero em-dashes in body (removed the one from line 5 during editing)\n\n3. **No Numbered Lists**: Use prose paragraphs, not bulleted or numbered lists in body content.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ No numbered lists\n\n#### Voice\n1. **No \"Trap\" Language**: Avoid \"trap\" as a noun.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Zero instances\n\n2. **No Strawmen**: Acknowledge the other side's valid arguments before dismantling them.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ The article fairly presents both EB-3 and TN as complementary, not competing\n\n3. **Killshot Idiom**: When killing a hypothetical, use \"Nice dream. But impractical.\"\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Not applicable — no hypothetical being killed (article resolves a binary, doesn't shoot down an idea)\n\n4. **No AI Vocabulary**: Avoid: \"nuanced,\" \"best practices,\" \"scalable,\" \"proactive,\" \"leverage,\" \"robust,\" \"ecosystem,\" \"synergy.\"\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Zero instances\n\n#### Paragraph Mechanics\n1. **Paragraph Density**: Never write exactly 3 sentences.\n   - **STATUS**: Need to check — let me scan for 3-sentence paragraphs\n\n2. **2x4-6 Expansion Technique**: Sentence structure guidance\n   - **STATUS**: Aspirational — not all paragraphs follow this exact template, but many do\n\n3. **Math as \"Aha!\"**: Numbers should be the payoff moment\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ The $40K-$80K vacancy cost and $200K-$400K EB-3 wait cost serve as payoff moments\n\n4. **Word Repetition**: Don't reuse the same word multiple times in close proximity.\n   - **STATUS**: Need to check — previously fixed \"that\" overuse, but let me verify\n\n#### Narrative Structure\n1. **Suspend-and-Pivot Intro**: Hook with visceral scene/pain point, pivot to stat/observation, then introduce solution.\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Opens with \"Your travel nurse invoice arrives every 13 weeks.\" (visceral), pivot to HR meeting treating EB-3/TN as binary, solution: \"The right visa pathway is the one that matches your actual staffing situation.\"\n\n2. **Narrative Headers**: Use story-chapter headers like \"The Acquisition Impasse\" — avoid \"Stats Spoilers.\"\n   - **STATUS**: ✅ Headers are narrative: \"You're Asking the Wrong Question\", \"The Math You've Never Seen Laid Out\", \"2026 Forecast: Reading the Bulletin Without a Law Degree\", \"The Right Answer Depends on the Question\"\n\n3. **Bridge Protocol**: Use transition words to connect paragraphs.\n   - **STATUS**: Need to check — let me scan for transition words at paragraph starts\n\nNow let me do the targeted checks I flagged:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_92bc925c-2c67-4495-b14d-ac6a59b04454","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && python3 -c \"\nimport re\ntext = open('/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Visa Pathway Comparison v3.md').read()\n# Split on double newline to get paragraphs\nparas = [p.strip() for p in text.split('\\n\\n') if p.strip()]\nprint(f'Total paragraphs: {len(paras)}')\n# Check for 3-sentence paragraphs\nthree_sent = []\nfor i, p in enumerate(paras):\n    # Simple sentence count by periods (not perfect but close)\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r'[.!?]+', p) if s.strip()]\n    if len(sentences) == 3:\n        three_sent.append((i+1, len(sentences), p[:100]))\nif three_sent:\n    print('\\\\n3-sentence paragraphs:')\n    for para_num, sent_count, preview in three_sent:\n        print(f'  Para {para_num}: {sent_count} sentences - {preview}...')\nelse:\n    print('\\\\nNo 3-sentence paragraphs found.')\n# Check for transition words at paragraph start\ntransitions = ['Furthermore', 'Consequently', 'Worse', 'Ultimately', 'Beyond', 'Once', 'Moreover', 'Therefore', 'However', 'Thus', 'Hence']\nmissing_trans = []\nfor i, p in enumerate(paras):\n    first_word = p.split()[0] if p.split() else ''\n    if first_word not in transitions and len(p) > 20:  # Skip very short paras\n        missing_trans.append((i+1, first_word, p[:50]))\nif missing_trans:\n    print('\\\\nParagraphs missing transition words (first 5):')\n    for para_num, first_word, preview in missing_trans[:5]:\n        print(f'  Para {para_num}: starts with \\\"{first_word}\\\" - {preview}...')\nelse:\n    print('\\\\nAll paragraphs start with transition words.')\n\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"nemotron-3-super:cloud","usage":{"input":55020,"output":1453,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56473,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite"