ne pipeline for speed and near-term coverage. One pipeline for permanence and long-term culture building. These tracks serve different populations, different timelines, and different strategic objectives, but they operate inside the same HR workflow and the same staffing plan. The parallel track approach is not a twice-as-hard version of choosing one pathway. It is a more sophisticated version of doing the right thing for the right reason on the right timeline.\n+63 Furthermore, the facility that is serious about solving its staffing problem runs both tracks simultaneously. One pipeline for speed and near-term coverage. One pipeline for permanence and long-term culture building. These tracks serve different populations, different timelines, and different strategic objectives, but they operate inside the same HR workflow and the same staffing plan. The parallel track approach is not a twice-as-hard version of choosing one pathway. It is a more sophisticated version of doing the right thing for the right reason on the right timeline.\n 64 \n 65 > There is no wrong choice between EB-3 and TN. There is only the choice that matches your actual staffing situation, and the choice to stop pretending only one track exists.\n 66 \n 67 Nava Healthcare runs both tracks. We have the TN pipeline for candidates who can move quickly, and the EB-3 pipeline for candidates where permanence is the objective. We don't think you should have to choose, and you don't. If you're ready to look at your staffing situation honestly and map it to the right immigration pathway, we can have that conversation today. No commitment required. Just the math.","firstChangedLine":63},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775061351478}}
{"type":"message","id":"da0cd8c7","parentId":"e0bd1912","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:35:57.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me do a final check to confirm the two main violations are fixed and see what remains:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_04af74c3-8cb4-41a7-8133-ff2be376a2ff","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && python3 -c \"\nimport re\ntext = open('/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Visa Pathway Comparison v3.md').read()\nparas = [p.strip() for p in text.split('\\n\\n') if p.strip()]\nprint(f'Total paragraphs: {len(paras)}')\n# Check for 3-sentence paragraphs\nthree_sent = []\nfor i, p in enumerate(paras):\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r'[.!?]+', p) if s.strip()]\n    if len(sentences) == 3:\n        three_sent.append((i+1, len(sentences), p[:100]))\nif three_sent:\n    print('\\\\n3-sentence paragraphs:')\n    for para_num, sent_count, preview in three_sent:\n        print(f'  Para {para_num}: {sent_count} sentences - {preview}...')\nelse:\n    print('\\\\n✓ No 3-sentence paragraphs found.')\n# Check for bold in body (not in headings or blockquotes)\nlines = text.split('\\n')\nbold_issues = []\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if '**' in line:\n        # Check if it's a heading (starts with #) or blockquote (starts with >)\n        stripped = line.strip()\n        if not (stripped.startswith('#') or stripped.startswith('>')):\n            bold_issues.append((i+1, line[:50]))\nif bold_issues:\n    print('\\\\nBold in body (not heading/blockquote):')\n    for line_num, preview in bold_issues:\n        print(f'  Line {line_num}: {preview}...')\nelse:\n    print('\\\\n✓ No bold in body (outside headings/blockquotes).')\n\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"nemotron-3-super:cloud","usage":{"input":63700,"output":444,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite