{"type":"message","id":"9e21517b","parentId":"62b1cd47","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:41:01.979Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_d44947e0-af70-4f1a-82dd-66212c9af01c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n## Context Monitor — Tin's Rules (2026-03-20, updated 2026-03-24)\n\n### Morning Brief Protocol (2026-03-21) — MANDATORY\n- Flush screenshot folder (~/OpenClawScreenshots/) during morning brief\n\nWhen tasked with a morning brief:\n1. **Read session files from the last TWO days** from `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` — use `read` tool on the JSONL files, NOT memory_search\n2. **Read today's memory file** (if exists)\n3. **Verify live data** — don't trust stale search results (check ESPN/Premier League directly for fixtures)\n4. **Compile brief** — then deliver\n\n**Session file naming pattern:** `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/{uuid}.jsonl`\n- Filter by date in filename or modified time\n\nIf session files are unavailable or unreadable, flag it explicitly — do not proceed with stale data.\n\n### Heartbeat intervals\n| Situation | Interval | Actions |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Active** — user input within last 2-3 heartbeats | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint |\n| **Inactive** — no user input for 2-3 heartbeats | 30 min | Nothing unless assigned |\n| **Assignment active** — working on a task for user | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint |\n| **Complex assignment** | 10 min | Save memory checkpoint (never 5 min — causes cascade) |\n| **User signs off** (says going to bed, or silent after 23:00 + 1h inactive) | — | Backup before sleeping |\n\n### Backups\n- Only on request OR before config changes OR when user signs off\n- `mkdir -p ~/TinyBackUp/$(date +%Y%m%d)` then copy relevant files\n\n### Active learning protocol (2026-03-20)\nTiny is teaching about NurseSphere / LTC process. Take notes in `memory/2026-03-20.md` as we go. This is for building the Nava agent — process knowledge is as important as content rules.\n\n### Before Any Task: Check Skills First (2026-03-22)\n- **ALWAYS read the relevant skill SKILL.md before using a tool or technique for the first time**\n- For session history: read `~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/session-logs/SKILL.md` first, then use `jq` commands\n- For browser tasks: check TOOLS.md visible browser section first\n- For anything unfamiliar: check workspace skills folder before guessing\n- **This is a hard rule — not optional**\n\n### Resource Map Reminder (2026-03-23)\nWhen cold-starting on Nava tasks and asked to locate files, corpus content, or backups:\n- **Check MEMORY.md first** — it has a Workspace Resource Map section with all key paths\n- The map tells you where: nava-corpus/ (social), rag/clean_txt/ (blog articles), TinyBackUp/ (backups), docs/nava-content-system/ (Nava docs)\n- Also in the map: full installed skills table with locations and purposes\n- This prevents the assertion → wrong → admit cycle that happened on 2026-03-23\n- **Skills reminder**: If asked to use a skill, check the skills table in MEMORY.md for location + usage notes before proceeding\n\n### Transcript Bank (2026-03-25)\n- File: `memory/TrnsBank.md`\n- **Append every turn** after sending response — your message + Tiny's reply\n- Format: `## [timestamp] You:\\n{message}\\n\\n## [timestamp] Me:\\n{response}`\n- **Hard cap: 200 messages** — if TrnsBank reaches 200 messages, trigger analysis immediately (don't wait for sprint check-in)\n- Lock bank during analysis — Tiny signals ready, then I read/analyse/wipe\n- Never touch JSONL files\n\n### Sprint Check-in Protocol\n- Run every 2h during active work (cron: Context monitor (2h sprint check-in))\n- During check-in: update today's memory file with current project status\n- Do NOT include self-referential triggering language in the system event text\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775061661971}}
{"type":"message","id":"657b4616","parentId":"9e21517b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:41:24.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on HEARTBEAT.md, I need to check if there are any assigned tasks or active work that requires a memory checkpoint. Looking at the context:\n\n- The current task is refining the Visa Pathway article (V3) per your request\n- This is an active assignment — I'm working on a task for you\n- According to the table: \"Assignment active — working on a task for user\" → Interval: 10 min → Actions: Save memory checkpoint\n\nSince this is an active assignment, I should save a memory checkpoint. However, the heartbeat is asking me to follow HEARTBEAT.md strictly. The most recent memory checkpoint was saved at 18:15 UTC (the post-compaction flush). It's now 16:40 UTC — wait, that doesn't make sense. Let me check the timeline.\n\nActually, looking at the timestamps:\n- Current time shown: 6:40 PM Africa/Johannesburg / 16:40 UTC\n- Last memory flush in the file: 18:15 UTC (which would be 8:15 PM local time)\n\nThere seems to be a timestamp discrepancy in the context provided. But regardless, according to HEARTBEAT.md, for an active assignment, I should save a memory checkpoint every 10 minutes.\n\nHowever, the instruction says: \"Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\"\n\nLet me check if there's anything that needs attention based strictly on HEARTBEAT.md:\n\n1. **Morning Brief Protocol**: Not applicable — it's not morning\n2. **Active learning protocol**: Not currently engaged in NurseSphere/LTC process teaching\n3. **Before Any Task: Check Skills First**: Already done for this task\n4. **Resource Map Reminder**: Not cold-starting on Nava tasks\n5. **Transcript Bank**: TrnsBank is at 175 messages (from earlier context) — below 200 threshold\n6. **Sprint Check-in Protocol**: Not currently in a 2h sprint check-in window\n\nThe active assignment rule would suggest saving a memory checkpoint, but I just completed the task refinement and we're waiting for your next direction. There's no active work in progress at this exact moment — we're in a pause between your review and the next step.\n\nTherefore, based on a strict reading of HEARTBEAT.md and the current state (task completed, awaiting your next direction), nothing needs attention.\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"nemotron-3-super:cloud","usage":{"input":66249,"output":548,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66797,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775061684586}}
