{"type":"message","id":"56b54af3","parentId":"bd169764","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:52:01.752Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_c385669e-0de8-4e7c-8ed4-eaee480510a1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, vacancy urgency serves as the primary temporal filter for pathway selection. Facilities requiring positions filled within six months cannot rely on EB-3 due to its minimum three-year timeline before investment math works, even under optimal processing conditions. TN provides the only realistic option for immediate needs, with arrival timelines of two to six months from process initiation.\nFurthermore, facilities should consult the World Health Organization for global healthcare workforce migration data, the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services for official processing time updates and policy guidance, and the Department of State for the monthly visa bulletin that serves as the foundational document for all EB-3 timeline forecasting and planning assumptions in the United States immigration system."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"Furthermore, vacancy urgency serves as the primary temporal filter for pathway selection. Facilities requiring positions filled within six months cannot rely on EB-3 due to its minimum three-year timeline before investment math works, even under optimal processing conditions. TN provides the only realistic option for immediate needs, with arrival timelines of two to six months from process initiation.\nFurthermore, facilities should consult the World Health Organization for global healthcare workforce migration data, the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services for official processing time updates and policy guidance, and the Department of State for the monthly visa bulletin that serves as the foundational document for all EB-3 timeline forecasting and planning assumptions in the United States immigration system.","cwd":"/h