{"type":"message","id":"a1cbe3ef","parentId":"d7d55394","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:20.749Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_cc1f9e88-77de-499a-b5da-0c3ee32a82a6","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"### Structure\n1. **2x4-6 Rule**: Each H3 section contains 2 paragraphs, each with 4-6 sentences. Applies to blog articles. Does NOT apply to: LinkedIn posts (use bold-for-pivots structure), X/twitter threads (one idea per tweet), or Statement of Trade (SoT) formats which follow different conventions.\n2. **H2 Introductions**: Every H2 heading must have a contextualizing paragraph immediately beneath it before H3s begin.\n3. **Blockquote Callouts**: Each H2 section ends with a blockquote axiom — the \"social media snippet\" that anchors the section's meaning.","old_string":"### Structure\n1. **2x4-6 Rule**: Each H3 section contains 2 paragraphs, each with 4-6 sentences.\n2. **H2 Introductions**: Every H2 heading must have a contextualizing paragraph immediately beneath it before H3s begin.\n3. **Blockquote Callouts**: Each H2 section ends with a blockquote axiom — the \"social media snippet\" that anchors the section's meaning.","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27358,"output":337,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27695,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775062880749}}
