{"type":"message","id":"d06bb7f1","parentId":"bdb3fdc1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:27.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_a7693c17-793e-4a1b-88d5-8ccab7d09d9a","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"### Paragraph Mechanics\n1. **Never Write Exactly 3 Sentences**: A 3-sentence paragraph is the most common AI drafting pattern and fails because it states a claim then stops before proving it. Always expand to 4-6 sentences with forensic depth, OR cut to 1-2 sentences if the thought is complete at that length. When in doubt, add a sentence — the extra detail is what separates good prose from AI filler.\n2. **Paragraph Density**: Never write exactly 3 sentences. Expand to 4-6 with forensic depth.","old_string":"### Paragraph Mechanics\n1. **Paragraph Density**: Never write exactly 3 sentences. Expand to 4-6 with forensic depth.","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27682,"output":226,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27908,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775062887950}}
{"type":"message","id":"585ab630","parentId":"d06bb7f1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:27.964Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_a7693c17-793e-4a1b-88d5-8ccab7d09d9a","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  94 3. **Killshot Idiom**: When killing a hypothetical, use \"Nice dream. But impractical.\" — never \"we stopped chasing X.\"\n  95 4. **No AI Vocabulary**: Avoid: \"nuanced,\" \"best practices,\" \"scalable,\" \"proactive,\" \"leverage,\" \"robust,\" \"ecosystem,\" \"synergy.\"\n  96 \n  97 ### Paragraph Mechanics\n- 98 1. **Paragraph Density**: Never write exactly 3 sentences. Expand to 4-6 with forensic depth.\n+ 98 1. **Never Write Exactly 3 Sentences**: A 3-sentence paragraph is the most common AI drafting pattern and fails because it states a claim then stops before proving it. Always expand to 4-6 sentences with forensic depth, OR cut to 1-2 sentences if the thought is complete at that length. When in doubt, add a sentence — the extra detail is what separates good prose from AI filler.\n+ 99 2. **Paragraph Density**: Never write exactly 3 sentences. Expand to 4-6 with forensic depth.\n  99 2. **2x4-6 Expansion Technique**:\n 100    - Sentence 1: The claim\n 101    - Sentence 2: The \"Why it happens\" (mechanism)\n 102    - Sentence 3: The math/evidence\n     ...","firstChangedLine":98},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775062887959}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0a4fb05","parentId":"585ab630","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:42.435Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_b3b6c496-d313-435d-a079-0bcace15f5fd","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"## Custom GPT Feedback — What It Catches (And What We Should Catch First)\n\nThe AbroadWorks Custom GPT provides a second-pass review. It consistently flags these categories of issues. We should catch these in self-edit BEFORE the draft goes to Custom GPT:\n\n### Mechanical Issues (Almost Always Caught)\n- Contractions in formal content (flagged as register inconsistency)\n- Em-dashes (flagged as non-standard punctuation)\n- Bold in body (flagged as formatting error)\n- Close-quote punctuation violations\n- Word repetition in close proximity\n- 3-sentence paragraphs\n\n### Immigration Factual Issues (Always Caught)\n- Outdated processing time claims\n- Visa bulletin designation confusion (Dates for Filing vs Final Action)\n- Incorrect EB-3 timeline ranges\n- Numbers used inconsistently with USCIS/NVC conventions\n\n### Structural Issues (Sometimes Caught)\n- Missing transitions between paragraphs\n- Paragraphs that feel like restatements of each other\n- H2 sections without contextualizing intro paragraphs\n- Missing blockquote callouts at end of H2 sections\n\n### What the Custom GPT Misses (Human Eye Catches)\n- The \"beautiful hypothetical\" that's easy to dismantle\n- Claims that sound plausible but lack Nava-specific grounding\n- Arguments that don't reflect how Tiny would actually write them\n- Tone that's technically correct but lacks the edge Tiny demands\n\n## LinkedIn Post Editor Rules","old_string":"## LinkedIn Post Editor Rules","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":27921,"output":384,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775062902434}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f523d2c","parentId":"d0a4fb05","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:42.459Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b3b6c496-d313-435d-a079-0bcace15f5fd","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 145 | Robust | Solid, Strong, Proven |\n 146 | Ecosystem | Environment, Network, System |\n 147 | Synergy | Alignment, Combined effect |\n 148 \n+149 ## Custom GPT Feedback — What It Catches (And What We Should Catch First)\n+150 \n+151 The AbroadWorks Custom GPT provides a second-pass review. It consistently flags these categories of issues. We should catch these in self-edit BEFORE the draft goes to Custom GPT:\n+152 \n+153 ### Mechanical Issues (Almost Always Caught)\n+154 - Contractions in formal content (flagged as register inconsistency)\n+155 - Em-dashes (flagged as non-standard punctuation)\n+156 - Bold in body (flagged as formatting error)\n+157 - Close-quote punctuation violations\n+158 - Word repetition in close proximity\n+159 - 3-sentence paragraphs\n+160 \n+161 ### Immigration Factual Issues (Always Caught)\n+162 - Outdated processing time claims\n+163 - Visa bulletin designation confusion (Dates for Filing vs Final Action)\n+164 - Incorrect EB-3 timeline ranges\n+165 - Numbers used inconsistently with USCIS/NVC conventions\n+166 \n+167 ### Structural Issues (Sometimes Caught)\n+168 - Missing transitions between paragraphs\n+169 - Paragraphs that feel like restatements of each other\n+170 - H2 sections without contextualizing intro paragraphs\n+171 - Missing blockquote callouts at end of H2 sections\n+172 \n+173 ### What the Custom GPT Misses (Human Eye Catches)\n+174 - The \"beautiful hypothetical\" that's easy to dismantle\n+175 - Claims that sound plausible but lack Nava-specific grounding\n+176 - Arguments that don't reflect how Tiny would actually write them\n+177 - Tone that's technically correct but lacks the edge Tiny demands\n+178 \n 149 ## LinkedIn Post Editor Rules\n 150 \n 151 LinkedIn posts follow different structural rules than blog articles. Apply this section when editing LinkedIn/X content.\n 152 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":149},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775062902453}}
{"type":"message","id":"f867f015","parentId":"4f523d2c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:01:55.887Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_a33fbdd2-169a-4175-ba43-3d41dc003f70","name":"edit","arguments":{"new_string":"### What Went Wrong (Draft 1-5 Analysis)\n- **Paragraph density wall**: Every paragraph was exactly 3 sentences — failed the 2x4-6 rule. Felt like \"claim then stop before proving it.\"\n- **Tone softness**: \"Most founders feel the pinch\" too conversational. Needed \"Street-Level Realism.\"\n- **Missing blockquotes**: Draft 4 had visceral intro but missed blockquote axioms at end of each H2 section.\n- **Wrong word choices**: Used \"Trap\" repeatedly — needed harder language like \"Executive Focus Penalty\" or \"Clerical Impasse.\"\n- **AI vocabulary leaks**: Used \"nuanced,\" \"best practices,\" \"scalable,\" \"proactive\" — flagged by humanizer (33/100).\n- **Phase jumping**: AWAA jumped from H1 selection straight to full draft without canvas approval — most repeated failure.\n- **Visa pathway article (v3)**: Used \"16 to 54 months\" for EB-3 (incorrect), em-dashes throughout, contractions in formal article, close-quote punctuation violations, bold labels in body. All caught by Custom GPT. Fixed in v4.","old_string":"### What Went Wrong (Draft 1-5 Analysis)\n- **Paragraph density wall**: Every paragraph was exactly 3 sentences — failed the 2x4-6 rule. Felt like \"claim then stop before proving it.\"\n- **Tone softness**: \"Most founders feel the pinch\" too conversational. Needed \"Street-Level Realism.\"\n- **Missing blockquotes**: Draft 4 had visceral intro but missed blockquote axioms at end of each H2 section.\n- **Wrong word choices**: Used \"Trap\" repeatedly — needed harder language like \"Executive Focus Penalty\" or \"Clerical Impasse.\"\n- **AI vocabulary leaks**: Used \"nuanced,\" \"best practices,\" \"scalable,\" \"proactive\" — flagged by humanizer (33/100).\n- **Phase jumping**: AWAA jumped from H1 selection straight to full draft without canvas approval — most repeated failure.","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/editor/SKILL.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":28310,"output":557,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28867,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775062915887}}
