andard; third source is article-specific\n+213 \n+214 ### Structural Requirements\n+215 - **H2 sections**: Each H2 must have a contextualizing intro paragraph (2-3 sentences) before any sub-content\n+216 - **Blockquotes**: Each H2 section ends with a blockquote axiom (provocative single sentence that sums the section's meaning)\n+217 - **No H3s required** — Nava blog articles use a flat H2 structure, not nested H2/H3\n+218 - **In-text links only** — markdown links embedded in body text, no URL footer list (exception: Sources section at bottom)\n+219 - **Bold**: Bold is for headings only. No bold in body text for labels or callouts.\n+220 \n+221 ### Mechanical Rules (Non-negotiable for Nava articles)\n+222 1. **Zero contractions** — \"do not\" not \"don't\", \"it is\" not \"it's\"\n+223 2. **Zero em-dashes** — use commas, semicolons, or separate sentences\n+224 3. **Zero en-dashes** — same rule as em-dashes\n+225 4. **Periods outside close-quotes for fragments** — `\"Current\"` not `\"Current.\"` when the quote ends a clause\n+226 5. **EB-3 timeline: 12 to 48 months** — not 16 to 54, not other ranges\n+227 6. **Premium processing: 15 business days** — not 45 calendar days\n+228 7. **Operational terms lowercase** — \"job embeddedness\" not \"Job Embeddedness\"\n+229 8. **No numbered lists in body** — Key Takeaways is the only exception; all body content is prose\n+230 \n+231 ### Transition Rules\n+232 - Never use \"Furthermore\" as a generic bridge — it reads as filler\n+233 - Use **diagnostic** transitions: \"From a budgetary perspective,\" \"The legal distinction lies in,\"\n+234 - Use **additive** transitions: \"In addition to urgency,\" \"Beyond the cost differential,\"\n+235 - Never start two consecutive paragraphs with the same word\n+236 \n 181 ## LinkedIn Post Editor Rules\n 182 \n 183 LinkedIn posts follow different structural rules than blog articles. Apply this section when editing LinkedIn/X content.\n 184 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":181},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064425147}}
