{"type":"message","id":"32c39c62","parentId":"78d28e5e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T00:00:18.301Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b227d623-9ebe-40d8-87c6-78bf664f1ed9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Git Repository Information\n\n**Last updated:** 2026-03-28\n\n---\n\n## Current State\n\nThe workspace git repository exists locally but has **no remote configured**.\n\n```bash\n# Current remotes (should show nothing):\ngit remote -v\n\n# Local branch:\ngit branch\n# → * main (or master)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Before You Need to Restore\n\nYou must set up a remote repository on GitHub or GitLab:\n\n### Option A — GitHub (recommended)\n\n1. Go to https://github.com and sign in\n2. Click **New repository** → name it `dawn-workspace`\n3. **DO NOT** initialize with README (empty repo)\n4. Copy the repository URL (e.g., `https://github.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git`)\n5. On your local machine, run:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git\ngit push -u origin main\n```\n\n### Option B — GitLab\n\n1. Go to https://gitlab.com and create an account\n2. Create a new project named `dawn-workspace`\n3. Add the remote and push:\n\n```bash\ngit remote add gitlab https://gitlab.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git\ngit push -u gitlab main\n```\n\n---\n\n## For Restore on a New Computer\n\nWhen rebuilding on a fresh machine:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Clone your repo\ngit clone https://github.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git workspace\n\n# 2. Enter the workspace\ncd workspace\n\n# 3. Pull latest\ngit pull origin main\n```\n\n---\n\n## Keeping Backups in Sync\n\nSince the workspace is pushed to git, your off-site backup IS GitHub/GitLab.\n\n**OneDrive still serves as:**\n- Backup of uncommitted files (session files, memory checkpoints)\n- Backup of openclaw.json (contains your tokens and private config)\n- Complete restore kit if GitHub becomes inaccessible\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- **Commit often** — every `git push` is an automatic off-site backup\n- **Session files** (JSONL) are NOT committed — they're in `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` locally and on OneDrive\n- **Browser profiles** are NOT committed — they're in `~/.openclaw/browser_profiles/` locally\n- **Node modules** are NOT committed — ignored by .gitignore\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775088018297}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa69c65f","parentId":"32c39c62","timestamp":"2026-04-02T00:00:52.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Restore kit needs rebuilding for Apr 2. Let me build it fresh.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_62230657-eee1-4fc8-be10-6ff9a1c0a344","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"BACKUP=\"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Apps/Dawn-Restore/20260402\"\nmkdir -p \"$BACKUP\"\n\n# Copy memory files\ncp -r /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ \"$BACKUP/memory/\"\necho \"Memory: $(find '$BACKUP/memory/' -type f | wc -l) files\"\n\n# Copy workspace (excluding .git, node_modules, browser_profiles, sessions)\ncd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace\nrsync -a --exclude='.git' --exclude='node_modules' --exclude='browser_profiles' --exclude='agents/main/sessions' . \"$BACKUP/workspace/\"\necho \"Workspace: $(find '$BACKUP/workspace/' -type f | wc -l) files\"\n\n# Copy openclaw.json\ncp /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/openclaw.json \"$BACKUP/openclaw.json\"\n\n# Generate fresh RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md\ncat > \"$BACKUP/RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md\" << 'ENDOFFILE'\n# Dawn Restore Instructions\n\n**Last updated:** 2026-04-02  \n**Purpose:** Rebuild everything on a fresh-out-of-the-box computer from scratch.\n\n---\n\n## What's Included\n\n- `memory/` — Daily memory files (continuity + learned rules)\n- `workspace/` — Full OpenClaw workspace (skills, agents, tools, configs)\n- `openclaw.json` — Gateway config (tokens, channels, cron jobs)\n- `RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md` — This file\n- `GIT_REPO.md` — Git remote setup instructions\n\n---\n\n## Step 1 — Install OpenClaw\n\nOn a fresh Windows machine:\n\n```powershell\nnpm install -g openclaw\n```\n\nOr via OpenClaw installer if available.\n\n---\n\n## Step 2 — Replicate WSL2 + Ollama Environment\n\nThis workspace assumes:\n- **WSL2** (Windows Subsystem for Linux 2)\n- **Ollama** running on Windows host at `localhost:11434`\n\nIf you need to set up Ollama on Windows:\n1. Download from https://ollama.com\n2. Install and pull models: `ollama pull minimax-m2.7`, `ollama pull gemma3:27b`\n\n---\n\n## Step 3 — Restore Your Workspace\n\n**Option A — From Git (recommended)**\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/dawn-workspace.git ~/.openclaw/workspace\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit pull origin main\n```\n\n**Option B — From Restore Kit**\n\n```bash\n# Extract zip to ~/.openclaw/workspace\n# Then restore memory + config\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 4 — Restore Config\n\n```bash\ncp openclaw.json ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 — Re-authenticate\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway start\n# Then re-link WhatsApp via QR code\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 6 — Verify Everything\n\n```bash\nopenclaw status\nopenclaw gateway status\n```\n\n---\n\n## What's NOT in This Kit\n\n- `agents/main/sessions/` — Session logs (large, personal, not needed for restore)\n- `browser_profiles/` — Browser automation profiles\n- `.git/` — Workspace git history\n- `node_modules/` — Installed packages (rebuilt via npm install)\n\n---\n\n## Key Files to Know\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `memory/MEMORY.md` | Long-term memory + identity |\n| `SOUL.md` | Who Dawn is |\n| `AGENTS.md` | Operating rules |\n| `skills/editor/SKILL.md` | Writing + editorial standards |\n| `TOOLS.md` | Environment-specific config |\n\n---\n\n## Workspace Git Remote\n\nThe workspace has a git remote. Set it up:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/dawn-workspace.git\ngit push -u origin main\n```\nENDOFFILE\n\n# Generate fresh GIT_REPO.md\ncat > \"$BACKUP/GIT_REPO.md\" << 'ENDOFFILE'\n# Git Repository Information\n\n**Last updated:** 2026-04-02\n\n---\n\n## Current State\n\nThe workspace git repository exists locally but has **no remote configured**.\n\n```bash\ngit remote -v\n# → (empty)\n\ngit branch\n# → * main (or master)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Before You Need to Restore\n\nYou must set up a remote repository on GitHub or GitLab:\n\n### Option A — GitHub (recommended)\n\n1. Go to https://github.com and sign in\n2. Click **New repository** → name it `dawn-workspace`\n3. **DO NOT** initialize with README (empty repo)\n4. Copy the repository URL\n5. Run:\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\ngit remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git\ngit push -u origin main\n```\n\n### Option B — GitLab\n\n```bash\ngit remote add gitlab https://gitlab.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git\ngit push -u gitlab main\n```\n\n---\n\n## For Restore on a New Computer\n\n```bash\n# 1. Clone your repo\ngit clone https://github.com/yourusername/dawn-workspace.git ~/.openclaw/workspace\n\n# 2. Pull latest\ngit pull origin main\n```\n\n---\n\n## Keeping Backups in Sync\n\nSince the workspace is pushed to git, your off-site backup IS GitHub/GitLab.\n\n**OneDrive still serves as:**\n- Backup of uncommitted files\n- Backup of openclaw.json (contains your tokens and private config)\n- Complete restore kit if GitHub becomes inaccessible\nENDOFFILE\n\necho \"--- All files copied ---\"\nls -la \"$BACKUP\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":29542,"output":1615,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31157,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775088052016}}
